- `¤ë (Ôş¿j, iÔş®)` if `j < i`

The measure `WignerMeasure ╬╝ ╬¢ n` is the product measure where each diagonal entry has measure `╬¢` and each off-diagonal entry has measure `╬╝`.

To prove the `HasLaw` statement, we need to show that the distribution of `(wignerMatrixMap n ¤ë) i j` under `WignerMeasure ╬╝ ╬¢ n` is `╬╝`.

